events.name: SPC x Talent Mafias: Instacart
events.description: ​South Park Commons is excited to partner with Max Mullen, cofounder of Instacart, to welcome several members of the "Instacart Mafia" to share how working at a talent dense company with an entrepreneurial culture influenced their early days of company building, what they're working on now, and visions for the future in an intimate fireside chat. Stick around afterwards to connect with SPC members and Instacart alumni over light refreshments.​Featuring​​​Max Mullen, Co-founder of Instacart​​​​Ofek Lavian, CEO of Forage​Praveen Chekuri, Co-founder of Ascend​Moderator: Finn Meeks, Partner at SPC​​Event Details​​​​​​​​​5:00pm:Doors open​​​5:30-6:15pm:Panel discussion​6:15-7pm:Networking​​South Park Commons is a home for the most talented technologists, builders, and domain-experts figuring out what's next—a community designed to turn the chaos of possibility into the clarity of conviction. Learn morehere.

events.name: -1 to Roblox with David Baszucki
events.description: ​South Park Commons is delighted to hostDavid Baszuckiof Roblox as part of our -1 to Now series!​​​​​Event Details​​​​​​​4:30pm: Doors Open​​​​5:00-6:00pm: Fireside Chat​David Baszucki​David Baszucki is the founder and CEO of Roblox. His vision is to build a platform that enables shared experiences among billions of users. The company has been widely recognized for its innovation and vision under Baszucki’s leadership.​TIME named Roblox one of the “100 Most Influential Companies,” and it has been recognized by Fast Company for innovation on their “Most Innovative Companies” and “Most Innovative Companies in Gaming” lists. Roblox was also recognized as an innovative workplace on Fast Company’s “Best Workplaces for Innovators” list and for its technical innovations on Fast Company’s “Innovation by Design” list.​Previously, David founded Knowledge Revolution, where he and his brother Greg created “Interactive Physics,” a leader in educational physics and mechanical design simulation software. David graduated from Stanford University as a General Motors Scholar in Electrical Engineering.​📢 -1 to Now is a recurring speaker series at South Park Commons exploring how the world's best builders and thinkers took their ideas from -1 to 0 and beyond. Join us for the inside stories of their experiments, pivots, and breakthroughs on the way to where they are today.​​Registration and approval is required and space is limited, so please RSVP soon.​​Please note doors close promptly at 5:30pm and there will be no late admittance.
